  "texts": [
    "BackgroundThis section reviews the existing literature on efforts to enhance the accuracy and reduce the hallucinations of LLMs, structured around four key themes that have emerged as critical in the discourse on language model development and optimization.",
    "Enhancing LLM AccuracyStudies have consistently shown that the accuracy of language models can be significantly improved through advanced Large language models (LLMs) have revolutionized the field of natural language processing (NLP), offering unprecedented capabilities in generating human-like text, understanding context, and answering questions across various domains [1,2].",
    "Among these models, Llama 2 7b, developed by Meta Inc., stands out due to its remarkable efficiency and accuracy, powered by 7 billion parameters.",
    "Such models have been instrumental in pushing the boundaries of what LLMs can achieve, providing researchers and developers with a versatile tool for a wide range of applications.",
    "However, despite its strengths, Llama 2 7b, like other LLMs, is not immune to the challenges that plague these advanced systems, particularly the issue of generating text that, while plausible, may not be grounded in factual accuracy, a phenomenon known as \"hallucination\" [2,3].Hallucination in LLMs poses significant c hallenges, especially when those models are used in scenarios requiring high levels of trust and accuracy, such as in news generation, educational content, and sensitive decision-making contexts [3]."
  ]
}